"Vijay Subramani" <vijay_is_here@vsnl.com> writes:
> 	How to trace a program which uses threads. gdb is useful for tasks which
> have a single thread of execution. Please let me know of any utility which
> does this.
If by "trace", you're talking about system call tracing (like 'strace'), you
may find SUBTERFUGUE useful.  It's still pretty alpha, but it can trace
threaded programs.
It's not a debugger, though.  (Not yet, anyway.  :-)
--Mike
